ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, I would recommend it to an NELC major.
I would recommend Egyptology 536 to another student- it was fun, interesting and rewarding.
Each week we translated one or several texts, and during class discussed our translation, with much of the discussion centered upon grammar and context for the text.
I would highly recommend taking the course, as it gives an unique opportunity to come in contact with materials and subjects which usually do not receive any attention.
Relaxed, encouraging classroom atmosphere. Discussion of the material extends beyond the purely grammatical. Fischer-Elfert is an excellent professor.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Since I am an undergrad, this question doesn't really pertain to me- it did help deepen my ability to understand and decipher hieroglyphics.
The course has deepened my knowledge of the Egyptian language and its usage in this specific genre.
